transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Olivia speaking.

Speaker 2: Who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 1: My name is Mark Lloyd.

Speaker 2: Hi, Mark. How are you?

Speaker 1: Hey, not too bad.

Speaker 2: Hey, listen, you guys had me on an auto order thing or something because I got another package in the mail from you, and I want to be removed from that list.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can help you with this.

Speaker 2: Okay, Mark. What is your date of birth?

Speaker 1: Fall 28, 1965.

Speaker 2: Perfect. And you're located in Sheboygan, Wisconsin?

Speaker 1: Yes, ma'am.

Speaker 2: Okay, great.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so I do see your prescription here.

Speaker 2: Just so you know, Mark, I do see that you have a ton of pills.

Speaker 1: You do always have the option, just so you know, if you don't want to receive regular orders with your prescription, you don't have to.

Speaker 2: You always have the option to place your prescription on hold for up to six months at a time, just because six months is when the prescription would expire if we didn't refill it.

Speaker 1: And the way that would work is you could still order during that duration of time.

Speaker 2: You just have to give us a call to place the order yourself.

Speaker 1: That would be fine.

Speaker 2: Okay, great.

Speaker 1: So, yeah, if you need anything before July 26, six months from now, just give us a call at this number Monday through Friday, 8-5 Pacific.

Speaker 2: We're always here.

Speaker 1: Okay, and so I won't get any next month, right?

Speaker 2: Correct. Definitely not, no.

Speaker 1: Okay, sounds good.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Thank you, Mark.

Speaker 2: I hope you have a great day.

Speaker 1: You too, Barb.

Speaker 2: Bye.
